Blake, 71, faces life in prison if convicted of killing Bakley.
Blake, 71, is charged with murder, two counts of solicitation of murder.
Blake is accused of murdering Bakley on May 4, 2001.
Blake, 71, a lifelong actor who starred in the 1970s TV detective show "Baretta," could face life in prison if convicted.
Both sides agree that Blake married Bakley because of their baby, Rosie, and then was determined to keep the child away from the mother who sold promises of sex by mail.
Blake, who is free on $1.5 million (euro1.14 million) bail, is charged with one count of murder, two counts of solicitation of murder and a special circumstance of lying in wait.
